---
layout: layouts/_base.njk
title: jplace's 11ty Starter
---

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% macro sectionHeader(moreClasses="") %}
<h2
  class="font-roboto font-medium text-section-header text-white leading-bound {{
    moreClasses
  }}"
>
  <!-- prettier-ignore -->
  {{ caller() }}
</h2>
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% endmacro %}

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% macro sectionDetails(moreClasses="") %}
<p class="font-open-sans text-section-detail text-black {{ moreClasses }}">
  <!-- prettier-ignore -->
  {{ caller() }}
</p>
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% endmacro %}

<section class="section bg-beige p-outer">
  <div>
    <p
      class="font-league-spartan text-header-sm text-aqua leading-none mb-base"
    >
      We all make mistakes!
    </p>
    <h1
      class="font-league-spartan text-header-lg text-black leading-none mb-md"
    >
      Navigating Pronouns<br />in the Workplace
    </h1>
    <p
      class="font-roboto font-medium text-header-md text-aqua leading-bound mb-md"
    >
      A guide to handling instances of<br />misgendering with grace
    </p>
    <p class="font-nunito text-header-xs text-black leading-tight">
      Content by Riley Pratt (<a href="#">@bae.witch</a>)<br />
      Design by Iris F (<a href="#">@sunny_side_vibes</a>)
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
<div class="separator one"></div>
<section class="section font-open-sans text-black bg-tan p-outer">
  <div class="adjusted-content">
    <div style="width: 60%;"></div>
    <div style="width: 40%;">
      {% call sectionHeader("mb-sm text-right") %} Catch yourself?<br />Correct
      yourself.
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% endcall %}
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% call sectionDetails("text-right") %}
      A <strong>quick correction</strong> validates that this was clearly a
      verable misstep, and not some deeper level of invalidating the person's
      identity.
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% endcall %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<div class="separator two reverse"></div>
<section class="section font-roboto text-white bg-aqua p-outer">
  <div class="adjusted-content">
    <div style="width: 40%;">
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% call sectionHeader("mb-sm") %}
      When should I step in if someone else makes a mistake?
      <em><span class="underline">Always.</span></em>
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% endcall %}
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% call sectionDetails() %}
      <em>Do not apologize.</em> An apology puts the onus on the misgendered
      person to make the speaker feel better rather than centering the resposne
      on the feelings of the person impacted.
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% endcall %}
    </div>
    <div style="width: 60%;"></div>
  </div>
</section>
<div class="separator three"></div>
<section class="relative section text-white bg-sunshine p-outer">
  <div class="adjusted-content">
    <div style="width: 60%;"></div>
    <div style="width: 40%;">
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% call sectionHeader("text-right mb-sm") %}
      Did someone correct you?<br />Just say
      <em>"<span class="underline">Thanks.</span>"</em>
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% endcall %}
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% call sectionDetails("text-right") %}
      <em>Do not apologize.</em> An apology puts the onus on the misgendered
      person to make the speaker feel better rather than centering the resposne
      on the feelings of the person impacted.
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% endcall %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <aside class="aside">
    <div class="relative">
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% call sectionHeader("mb-sm") %}
            Ask. Don't<br />assume.
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% endcall %}
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% call sectionDetails() %}
            Normalizing asking for someone's pronouns is important and helps trans and
        non-binary people everywhere!
      <!-- prettier-ignore -->
      {% endcall %}
    </div>
  </aside>
</section>
